HEADWORD: Swinish
<hw>Swin"ish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to swine; befitting swine; like swine; hoggish; gross; beasty; <as>as, a <ex>swinish</ex> drunkard or sot</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Swinish</xex> gluttony.⟦rdquo⟧  <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj> -- <wordforms><wf>Swin"ish*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> -- <wf>Swin"ish*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

